<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910311-0033</DOCNO><DOCID>910311-0033.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- BSN Corp.:   Concern Says It Has Offer   Of $55 Million for 2 Lines</HL><DATE>03/11/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8D</SO><CO>   BSN</CO><IN>SPECIALTY APPAREL RETAILERS (SAP)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   BSN Corp., Dallas, said it received an offer to buy itssporting goods catalog and football-equipment businesses forabout $55 million.   The sporting-goods maker said its board will review theproposal and probably will respond this week. It didn'tidentify the suitor but said it is a large New York financialfirm.</LP><TEXT>   Michael Blumenfeld, president, said the company hired aninvestment banker last year to look at the possibility ofselling some businesses. BSN received several offers butdidn't accept any, he said. Instead, BSN said last week thatit plans to offer 71% of its Sport Supply Group unit, thecatalog business, to the public and use the proceeds to paybank debt.   Mr. Blumenfeld said the company plans to go forward withthat offering while the offer to buy the businesses is underconsideration. In addition to the two businesses, BSN has atrophy business as well as cash and other assets.</TEXT></DOC>